<br>
At Stealth spec 32 (double the Detect Hidden spec), we could get Blending, which puts a maximum range on our detection just a bit larger than the current minimum detect radius.  The upshot would be a 50 assassin will see another 50 assassin just a little bit before anyone else, but a 50 assassin will see a 50 archer/minstrel long before that.<br>
<br>
That way we have the advantage in trying to find other stealthy types, without completely negating our ability to approach each other.<br>
<br>
Any high-level assassin serious about their ability to hide will have more than 32 Stealth, so there shouldn't be a need for anyone to respec. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ebullition>Ebullition</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/02 11:28:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=97>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden test results, v1.45b</span><hr size=1> In the new letter from Mark Jacobs he talks about having skills that come from Realm Points.<br>
